Parliament, Monday, 8 October 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Transport will on Tuesday receive a briefing from the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (Prasa) on the burning of trains and a strategy the entity has in dealing with the challenge. The Chairperson of the Board, Ms Khanyisile Kweyama, is expected to lead Prasa’s delegation. Venue: Townhouse Hotel
	Time: 09h30 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORT, MS DIKELEDI MAGADZI. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer:
	
